  "prompt": "Where can I learn live gesture recognition as a college student?",
  "response": "As a college student interested in learning live gesture recognition, here are several resources and approaches:\n\n1. Online Courses\n- Coursera: Computer Vision and Machine Learning courses\n- edX: AI and Computer Vision classes\n- Udacity: Deep Learning Nanodegree\n- Udemy: Gesture Recognition specific courses\n\n2. University Resources\n- Take computer vision or machine learning courses\n- Join research labs focused on gesture recognition\n- Participate in computer science project groups\n- Attend workshops/seminars on AI and vision technologies\n\n3. Programming Platforms\n- OpenCV tutorials for gesture recognition\n- TensorFlow and Keras deep learning frameworks\n- MediaPipe (Google's gesture recognition library)\n- PyTorch tutorial sections\n\n4. GitHub Projects\n- Open-source gesture recognition repositories\n- Collaborative machine learning projects\n- Study existing implementation codes\n\n5. Technical Conferences/Workshops\n- CVPR (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition)\n- ICCV (International Conference on Computer Vision)\n- Local AI/ML meetups\n\n6. Learning Libraries\n- Scikit-learn\n- Keras\n- Numpy/Pandas\n- OpenCV Python\n\nRecommended learning path: Start with basic computer vision, progress to machine learning, then specialize in gesture recognition techniques.",
